text: wandering back and forth in a building that's literally a mile long.
My strategy of fighting jet lag by progressively staying up later and later in advance of travel seems to be working. So far.
Every time I think my life can't get any more insane, the world gets definitively, dramatically more crazy. I *think* it's a good thing.
@wilw please specify goatse *t-shirt* -- it sounds a lot worse if you just say I did "a goatse thing".
Any product, no matter how useless or obscure, becomes far more appealing when reduced to Travel Size.
My generation ends at precisely the point when females started feeling compelled to make kissy face every time they're photographed.
@fastcompany did solid work with http://tinyurl.com/7a6557 (happily including mentions of @dollarshort, @leahculver and @sixapart)
"In order to ensure consistent service, all customers will be subjected to equally interminable hold times."
Big ideas, tall buildings, ambitious people. Today is a day full of New York things.
I think Beyonce should just use the footage of the First Dance as the video for her single release of At Last.
My sense is that the international perception of today is more akin to the moon landing than to any past inauguration.
I have to say, even just seeing a new whitehouse.gov with a blog on the homepage makes me happy.
perfect -- my gloves and hat have become unlost just in time for a pretty snowfall. winter!
When Obama is president, HBO will be free.
In one block I walked by people talking about making a film, an album, and a painting. Recessions really are a bull market for artists.
I was having a relatively good day and then @djacobs reminded me that Aaliyah would have turned 30 today. I hate that guy!
@ginatrapani http://lifehacker.com/5132674/ succinctly sums up why you're the best at what you do. :) Congrats!
This was a bad week to have misplaced my hat and gloves somewhere.
Do not let people mislabel the US Air landing a "miracle". It was the result of education, experience, skill and competence. Not magic.
I'm really struck by how much people want to *announce* the US Air plane crash (and rescue), even if people already know. Interesting urge.
@twitter I will pay you $14.50 to replace @stevenbjohnson with me as a suggested user when people sign up for Twitter. #freebusinessmodel
Everybody was making fun of my beat up old phobe but they don't know it's only banged up because I TALK SO HARD MY PHONE GETS BRUISED.
I ordered four shackburgers, three fries, two drinks and a cheeseburger, and he asked if it was to stay or to go. Even though I'm alone.
Today is my wife's birthday, the day each year when I must confront that she is both more mentally mature and younger-looking than me.
To the Hare Krishna trying to greet me with "Hello, Brother!" just a little note: I ain't your brother. Go on with your bongo drums.
Sanjay Gupta must have gotten word that I'm gunning for best-known Indian media guy and decided to step up his game. C. Everett Koop my ass.
@kanyewest I am really serious, I think you should reach out to P.M. Dawn. We need them back in our lives, and only you can help.
Our fridge sometimes emits a plaintive whine exactly like the intro to Jeff Buckley's "Lover, You Should've Come Over". This pleases me.
Just realizing, I am speculating about enemies placing curses on me, yet I don't know who my enemies are. Reveal yourselves, secret foes!
I inexplicably have that "lime in the coconut" song stuck in my head, so whichever of my enemies put a curse on me: it worked!
Now I just need a resolution that works as well as last year's did. Of course, my 2008 resolution was "Be Less Forgiving", so that was easy.
Happy birthday to my friends born on January 1 and to everybody who signs up for websites but leaves their birthdate as 1/1 due to laziness.
